---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — ZC">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="page-header">
      <a href="" class="back-link">← Home</a>
      <h1>About</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="col">

      <!-- Intro -->
      <p class="about-lead fade-up fade-up-1" style="font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        I'm transitioning into implementation consulting and solutions architecture. 
        This site is how I'm doing it - building in public, documenting everything, 
        and being honest about what works and what doesn't.
      </p>

      <p class="fade-up fade-up-2">
        My background is Web and Marketing Technologies. I started this structured 
        learning track in Dec 2025 with a 6–12 month window to build the 
        technical and communication skills that IC and SA roles actually need.
      </p>

      <p class="fade-up fade-up-2">
        This isn't a CV. The projects here are real attempts at real problems — 
        some shipped, some stalled, some got killed. Every one gets a write-up. 
        The goal is to show how I think and learn, not just what I delivered.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <!-- Why IC and SA -->
      <h2 style="font-size: 1rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        Why IC &amp; SA
      </h2>

      <p>
        Implementation consultants and solutions architects sit at the intersection 
        of technical systems and human problems. They translate between engineers 
        and stakeholders, design how products get adopted, and own the outcome 
        when things go sideways.
      </p>
      <p>
        That combination — systems thinking, clear communication, knowing when 
        to build versus configure versus integrate — is what I'm working toward. 
        The skills aren't taught in a course. They're built through doing.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <!-- Learning phases -->
      <h2 style="font-size: 1rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 1.75rem;">
        The track
      </h2>

      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0;">

        <!-- Phase 1 -->
         
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr; gap: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); opacity: 0.6;">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Phase 01</div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--text3); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Months 1–3</div>
            <span class="badge badge-archived">Completed</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Foundations</div>
            <ul class="skill-list">
              <li>SQL — querying, joining, aggregating real datasets</li>
              <li>Python — pandas, file I/O, basic scripting</li>
              <li>Diagramming — Mermaid, process and system maps</li>
              <li>Technical writing — documenting decisions for humans</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Phase 2 -->
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr; gap: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Phase 02</div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--text3); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Months 4–6</div>
            <span class="badge badge-live">Current</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Application</div>
            <ul class="skill-list">
              <li>REST APIs — connecting to and consuming real data sources</li>
              <li>Workflow automation — n8n, Make, GitHub Actions</li>
              <li>Node.js or deeper Python — building simple tools end-to-end</li>
              <li>Storytelling — translating technical work into business impact</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Phase 3 -->
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr; gap: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); opacity: 0.4;">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Phase 03</div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--text3); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Months 7–9</div>
            <span class="badge badge-archived">Upcoming</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Composition</div>
            <ul class="skill-list">
              <li>AI integration — Claude API, prompt engineering, RAG patterns</li>
              <li>Architecture thinking — system design, integration mapping</li>
              <li>Lightweight tools — full input-to-output products with live URLs</li>
              <li>Documentation — README, handover docs, client-ready write-ups</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Phase 4 -->
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 140px 1fr; gap: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem 0; opacity: 0.3;">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Phase 04</div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--text3); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Months 10–12</div>
            <span class="badge badge-archived">Upcoming</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Consolidation</div>
            <ul class="skill-list">
              <li>Polish the anchor project end-to-end</li>
              <li>Full post-mortems on every major technical decision</li>
              <li>Present the body of work as a coherent narrative</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <hr />

      <!-- How this site works -->
      <h2 style="font-size: 1rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        How this works
      </h2>

      <p>
        45–60 minutes on weekdays, more on weekends. Each session has a 
        pre-decided focus — SQL day, Python day, build day — to avoid 
        decision fatigue when time is short.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every project gets a card. Every significant session gets a build 
        log entry. The format is consistent: what I was trying to do, 
        what actually happened, what I'd do differently. Killed projects 
        stay on the site. Honest write-ups are the point.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <!-- Contact -->
      <h2 style="font-size: 1rem; font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--text3); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        Get in touch
      </h2>

      <div style="display: flex; gap: 2rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="https://github.com/ZackC98" target="_blank"
           style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text2); letter-spacing: 0.05em;">
          GitHub ↗
        </a>
        <a href="https://x.com/yourhandle" target="_blank"
           style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text2); letter-spacing: 0.05em;">
          X ↗
        </a>
        <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/yourprofile" target="_blank"
           style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text2); letter-spacing: 0.05em;">
          LinkedIn ↗
        </a>
        <a href="mailto:you@email.com"
           style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text2); letter-spacing: 0.05em;">
          Email ↗
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
